div.p:
4o. The Pannal did refuſe to ſend for a Chyrurgion, and to let his Father's
Body be ſighted, though the Miniſter, and others did expreſly demand it;
and the Engliſh-men in the Manufactory, who were acquainted with the Crowner-Laws,
they made a mutiny anent the Burial, till the Corps were ſighted;
yet the Pannal cauſed bury the Corps that ſame night without ſhewing them.
